5-Card component


App specific funtionality to each component

1-in the App component pass this.state.monster as a prop
to the CarList component, and move the mapping capability into
the CardList component as well.

-in the CardList component map through the monsters array getting t
the data from the props.monster...

2-create the Card component
create a folder inside the componentes folder
and a file inside it called Card.jsx

-- add the key in the CardList component:

<div className="card-list">
      {props.monsters.map(monster => (
        <Card key={monster.id} monster={monster} />
      ))}
    </div>


-card-style.css:

-create a card-style.css and add:


.card-container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  background-color: #95dada;
  border: 1px solid gray;
  border-radius: 5px;
  padding: 25px;
  cursor: pointer;
  -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
  backface-visibility: hidden;
  transform: translateZ(0);
  transition: transform 0.25s ease-out;
}

.card-container:hover {
  transform: scale(1.05);
}

3-add an img and an email tag inside the Card component:

<div className="card-container">
    <img
      src={`https://robohash.org/${props.monster.id}?set=set3&size180x180`}
    />
    <h1>{props.monster.name}</h1>
    <p>{props.monster.email}</p>
  </div>

